headline.main: GEORGE M. COHAN, 64, DIES AT HOME HERE; Veteran Actor, Producer and Playwright Called Himself 'a Song-and-Dance Man'

snippet: George M. Cohan, the Yankee Doodle Dandy of the American stage who gave his country its greatest song of the first World War, died yesterday at 5 A.M. in his home overlooking Central Park. His death climaxed more than a year's painful illness and ...
